Package org.neo4j.internal.batchimport.staging

Interface Step<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of batch objects received from upstream.
    All Superinterfaces:
    AutoCloseable, Panicable, Parallelizable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractStep, BatchFeedStep, CacheGroupsStep, CalculateDenseNodesStep, CountGroupsStep, DataImporter.ControllableStep, DeleteDuplicateNodesStep, EncodeGroupsStep, ForkedProcessorStep, IdMapperPreparationStep, LabelIndexWriterStep, LonelyProcessingStep, NodeSetFirstGroupStep, ProcessorStep, ProcessRelationshipCountsDataStep, ProducerStep, PullingProducerStep, ReadGroupRecordsByCacheStep, ReadGroupsFromCacheStep, ReadNodeIdsByCacheStep, ReadRecordsStep, RecordProcessorStep, RelationshipLinkbackStep, RelationshipLinkforwardStep, RelationshipLinkStep, RelationshipTypeIndexWriterStep, UpdateRecordsStep
    public interface Step<T>
extends Parallelizable, AutoCloseable, Panicable
    One step in Stage, where a Stage is a sequence of steps. Each step works on batches. Batches are typically received from an upstream step, or produced in the step itself. If there are more steps downstream then processed batches are passed down. Each step has maximum "work-ahead" size where it awaits the downstream step to catch up if the queue size goes beyond that number. Batches are associated with a ticket, which is simply a long value incremented for each batch. It's the first step that is responsible for generating these tickets, which will stay unchanged with each batch all the way through the stage. Steps that have multiple threads processing batches can process received batches in any order, but must make sure to send batches to its downstream (i.e. calling receive(long, Object) on its downstream step) ordered by ticket.
